history.text: Hi! Have you had a chance to see the movie, John Wick?
I just finished it. It wasn't bad.
I like action movies. Do you?
I love action movies especially with a story. This background story was a bit thin but it works.
I totally agree. The plot was barely there but the action was great!
What did you think of Keanu Reeves?
Oh, he was all right. He is kind of a blah actor but he did the action scenes well. I liked the Ms. Perkins character though
Keanu was totally dead pan. He relentlessly pursued the Russian mob. What did you think of his focus?
He was certainly focused on the car and the poor puppy. I don't know if that's deadpan or dumb honestly... but it works okay.
(have you gotten a second paragraph of text yet?)
It is so true. He was will do die for the dog and the car.  I believe that was somewhat deliberate.
the whole russian mob in new york city is a bit played out though.
they tried to use it to create a plot but it was so predictable
What did you think of the Russian mobster's son stealing the car and taking it to the shop that the owner knew it was John Wick's?
very predictable. i could almost recite the dialog without having seen it.
i like knowing the back story of how john and helen got married though
I thought the father was a very convincing Russian mobster.
he was. just like the godfather
I was thinking the same thing. He knew his son was wrong but he stood by him and was almost forced to fight John Wick.
viggo must have been surprised when john was able to complete the impossible task
I love the part where John is at the hotel and Ms Perkins tries to kill him.
yeah, that was good action. but i don't like watching men beat up women. i'm glad it wasn't too graphic.
i don't know why john had to destroy viggo's money though. you'd think he could do something better with it.
The part of Mrs Perkins was a bit like James Bond. I think the burning of the money was to hurt the Mob and make the point that he couldn't be bought.
i've never actually seen a james bond movie, but i'll take your word for it
yes, burning the money always pisses off the mob
I also liked the hotel desk clerk, Marcus. He was discreet and helped John .
and the new dog at the end... always coming full circle. a typically american ending
I think after all of the violence, it shows redeeming qualities in John Wick.
i guess so, but that was already made clear by his wanting out of the underworld
i guess it shows his determination to stay out
Did you have a favorite part of the story?
i liked the ending. that's where it all comes together and is tied up with a neat little bow. how about you?
I thought the fight with Ms Perkins was good and especially that he did not kill her.
And yes the puppy at the end was so fitting
